Graded Project 1 - Python for Data Science¶

Problem Statement ¶

Analyse & formulate a report for the Football Team Selection.¶

A new football club named GL United FC has just been inaugurated. This club does not have a team yet. The team is looking to hire players for their roster. Management wants to make such decisions using a data based approach. During a recent hiring drive, you were selected for the Data Science team as a data scientist. Your team has been tasked with creating a report which recommends players for the main team.

Dataset Description:¶

The data contains details for over 18,000 players playing in various football clubs in Europe. It contains information on age, skill rating, wages and player value, etc. The files provided are as follows:

  • fifa.csv data file.
  • fifa_ variable_information.csv - information on individual variables.

## ii) average overall rating of Top10 Clubs using a plot

best_dict = {}
for club in result_df['Club'].unique():
    overall_rating = result_df['Overall'][result_df['Club'] == club].mean()
    best_dict[club] = overall_rating
    
best_club = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(best_dict, orient = 'index', columns = ['overall'])
best_club['club'] = best_club.index
best_club = best_club.sort_values(by = 'overall', ascending =  False)

plt.figure(1 , figsize = (15 , 6))
sns.barplot(x ='club', y ='overall', data = best_club.head(10), palette = 'rocket')  
plt.xticks(rotation = 30)

plt.xlabel('Club', fontsize = 14)
plt.ylabel('Average Overall Rating of players in club', fontsize = 14)
plt.title('Clubs with best Players (average of overall ratings of players per club)', fontsize = 16)
plt.ylim(0 , 100)

plt.show()

  • Dataframe is generated with data like "Player name", "Club Name", "Wage" and "Overall rating".
  • Average of overall rating was calculated for each unique club.
    • Average value lies between 53.65 - 82.28
  • Average overall rating of players from top 10 clubs is retrieved and plotted as bar chart.
  • From the plot, it is observed that:
    • 'Juventus' club has the highest average rating of 82.28
    • 'FC Bayern Munchen' club ranks 10th with average rating of 77.0
    • Top 10 clubs are also visible and derived in plot

20. Generate a data frame containing top 5 players by Overall rating for each unique position.¶

In [43]:
## dataframe of top 5 players by Overall rating for each unique Position


def top_position_uniq(val):
    for pos in fifa_df['Position'].unique():
        top_overall_rating = fifa_df['Overall'][fifa_df['Position'] == pos].head(5)
        i = 0
        res1_df = {}
        for i in range(5):
            res1_df[i] = top_overall_rating.index[i]
            i = i+1
        
        best_pos_df1 = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(res1_df, orient='index', columns = ['index'])
        
        if str(val) is 'df':
            print('---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------')
            print('Dataframe of top 5 players based on Overall rating with Position : ' + pos)
            display(fifa_df.loc[best_pos_df1['index']])
            print('---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------')
            print()
            print()
        else:
            sample_df = fifa_df.loc[best_pos_df1['index']]
            print(sample_df.groupby('Position')[['Wage']].mean().T)
